first products later that year the company received funding from foundation capital thomas weisel venture partners signal peak ventures frazier technology ventures and cisco systems prior to its august   ipo current ceo martin plaehn joined control in september  products and servicesedit control’s home automation systems have been likened to an operating system for the home the company develops a branded line of products and services to control home lighting multiroom audio and hvac systems that utilize communication protocols such as zigbee wifi bluetooth and zwave control also supports more than  devices from thirdparty manufacturers including the nest smart home thermostat  coolmasternet for seamless integration with vrf  split hvacs sonos music system and products from sony and subzero for example with control a homeowner could control “the ventilation in his garage the music streaming to speakers in multiple rooms of his home every light the tv the thermostat even the bluray player in the guest house” from an ios device in  control released its simple device discovery protocol sddp which makes products embedded with the code automatically discoverable on a control network the company licenses the protocol which is similar to universal plug and play to other vendors for their products such as sony bravia tvs as of january  over  developers supported sddp in more than  devices including panasonic dish network bose tivo epson harman kardon denon pioneer sony sharp and yamaha as of february  control was selling its products through a network of  north american and  international authorized dealers in  countries in  the following dealers were honored with  dealer of the year awards emea – audiotek sarl spain – arbona piza france – futur in media portugal – deritec gcc – mega tech italy – tesis london – aonyx sweden – hages radio tv switzerland – olvision sagl ireland – cloney audio benelux – bg audio video solutions bv additionally control partners with national homebuilders including toll brothers to provide optional home automation packages to homebuyers proprietary productsedit audiovideo  a line of audio and video distribution products for controlling entertainment throughout a home using a centralized source lighting  wireless programmable lighting control systems controlled by switches dimmers keypads and remote devices hvac  smart thermostats compatible with most hvac systems worldwide and remotely controllable touch screens  touch screens handheld and stationary that operate as dedicated interfaces for control systems remote controls  remote controls that enable control of an entire smart home system controllers  main device connecting and controlling the entire system sensorsrelays  motion and light sensors to automatically initiate actions within the system like turning on the lights when you enter a room cameras  security cameras for video intercoms or “door stations” networking  following the acquisition of pakedge in march  referencesedit  the control experience controlcom control retrieved  march    a b jacobson julie  august  control up  on first day of ipo how did they get there cepro cepro retrieved  march    about control controlcom control retrieved  march    jacobson julie  june  introducing control automation vets plan ‘unrivaled’ product launch cepro cepro retrieved  march    a b fehrenbacher katie  july  connected home startup control files for an ipo for up to m gigaom gigaom retrieved  march    control names martin plaehn president  chief executive officer controlcom control retrieved  march    lamonica martin  february  cisco ties knot with control for smart home cnet cnet retrieved  march    jacobson julie  may  control aims to be ‘os’ of the automated home cepro cepro retrieved  march    a b c jacobson julie  january  control ceo on home automation standards diy pro install cepro cepro retrieved  march    control uses embedded sddp technology to provide smart home solution for panasonic’s new k ultr